<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/2025-06-14-an-inescapable-truth.gif" alt="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Ambigramme_de_Georges_Perec_-_andin_basnoda_a_une_epouse_qui_pue_-_animation.gif" width="960" height="960" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-70960" /></p>
<p>Georges Perec worked out that the French phrase <em>andin basnoda a une epouse qui pue</em> (&#8220;Andin Basnoda has a smelly wife&#8221;) reads the same upside down.</p>
<p>Typographer Pierre di Sciullo created a typeface to honor this ambigram &#8212; he called it Basnoda.</p>
